   <body>
      <context>
         <p>Use the <uicontrol>Validate</uicontrol> action to ensure that all smart fields in your document
            are in the proper format for their assigned data type (e.g., Date, Number, DateTime,
            selected values from picklists,etc.). The agreement document cannot be reconciled at
            check-in unless all fields in your document are valid.</p>
         <p>To validate fields:</p>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Go to <menucascade>
                  <uicontrol>Document </uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol>Fields</uicontrol>
               </menucascade>.</p>
            <p>
               <fig>
                  <image height="250"
                         placement="break"
                         width="262"
                         href="../attachments/45220124/49086833.png"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click on the <uicontrol>Validate</uicontrol> button. </p>
            <stepresult>
               <p>If any fields are invalid, the field row in the Document pane will be highlighted
                  in red.</p>
               <fig id="fig_wdq_psn_12c">
                  <image height="250"
                         placement="break"
                         width="284"
                         href="../attachments/45220124/50036846.png"
                         id="image_xdq_psn_12c"/>
               </fig>
            </stepresult>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Make any corrections to invalid fields as needed and click
                  <uicontrol>Validate</uicontrol> again to confirm there are no invalid fields.
            </p>
         </li>
      </ol>
      <result id="result_igq_rsn_12c">
         <p>If all fields are valid, a success message is displayed at the bottom of the pane. You
            can now check in your document.</p>
         <fig id="fig_bcg_tsn_12c">
            <image height="400"
                   placement="break"
                   href="../attachments/45220124/50036842.png"
                   id="image_ccg_tsn_12c"/>
         </fig>
      </result>
